The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, March 14, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, March 13: The countrys foreign exchange reserves surged $772 million to touch record levels of $109.13 billion even as gold reserves declined by $99 million for the week ended March 5. Following fresh inflows and revaluation of the dollar vis-a-vis other currencies, the foreign exchange reserves, which include gold reserves, grew to $1,09,132 million, according to the Reserve Bank of Indias weekly statistical bulletin released here today. The foreign currency assets rose by $871 million to touch $1,04,940 million.																								 New Delhi, March 13: Disinvestment minister Arun Shourie today came out strongly in favour of a radical restructuring of the countrys system of governance by drastically reducing the functions of the government. He said the government had become like an ocean covering all spheres of life and this had led to the entire system getting bogged down in red-tape. 
